libbtc
------------------------------------------
Libbtc is a very portable C library for creating and manipulating bitcoin data
structures and interacting with the p2p network.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.0-0.203.gf78009cb1ccf
  libbtc-devel-0.1+git20210429-1bl1
  libbtc0-0.1+git20210429-1bl1
  libevent2.1_7-2.1.12-1
  liblogdb0-0.1+git20160906-1bl3
  libsecp256k1_2-0.5.1-1bl1
  pkg-config-2.3.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  autoconf-archive-2023.02.20-1
  automake-20240607-1
  binutils-2.43.1-1
  cygport-0.36.9-1
  gcc-core-12.4.0-3
  gcc-g++-12.4.0-3
  libevent-devel-2.1.12-1
  liblogdb-devel-0.1+git20160906-1bl3
  libsecp256k1-devel-0.5.1-1bl1
  libtool-2.5.3-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/libbtc/libbtc

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/libbtc/libbtc.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libbtc-0.1+git20210429-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libbtc-0.1+git20210429-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libbtc-0.1+git20210429-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbtc-0.1+git20210429-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbtc0-0.1+git20210429-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbtc-devel-0.1+git20210429-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libbtc)
  /usr/bin/bitcoin-send-tx.exe
  /usr/bin/bitcoin-spv.exe
  /usr/bin/bitcointool.exe
